caption: This is my first time trying seafood boil and I must say I love it. I got 1/2 pound of the dungeness crab and it was amazing. The crab was big and very enjoyable. They have an open kitchen concept where you can watch them as the food is being prepared. The staff is very friendly and welcoming. Would try this place again.
I like its food very much. The service is very good. The seafood is very fresh. The open kitchen showed me that the chefs were friendly and hygienic

First time in the restaurant and it would be my last!!!!! The short cook did not use a glove while transferring my fries into the bowl. Not only that some fries fell on the ground where he pick them up and dropped them into the oil. I said something to both the cook and the lady that was taking the orders.
I got the combo with 1lb shrimp and 1lb Lobster tail. They taste fresh, and the shrimp was larger than expected. Great value for some yummy seafood boil.
Delicious, just ordered from here, thrilled to have a fast solid Cajun place in the neighborhood.  Can’t wait to order again!

I've ordered twice from this new-to-our-neighborhood spot. Incredible!!! I've tried the Snow crab with scallops, King crab and scallops with different styles. NOT OVERCOOKED! I'm a new regular. I hate overcooked seafood. I love seafood!!!

Glad to have a new seafood spot in the area. I decided to try it today. I ordered an order of Dungeness crab, crawfish and black mussels. The price is relatively great compared to other seafood places. The seafood is fresh and juicy with a lot of sauce and the people there are friendly. I will be stopping by again.

Relatively new spot in the area. I decided to try it out and loved it. I got the lobster boil and 1 cluster of snow crab in garlic butter spicy. I enjoyed every bit of it. The seafood was fresh and they had a nice atmosphere. I definitely recommend for everyone to try them out.
